description.narrative: IR 2.4 By 2013, in 10 provinces, 30% under five children and pregnant and lactating women have access to and utilise quality community and facility based interventions for the prevention and management of malnutrition (Acute severe malnutrition, stunting and micronutrient deficiencies)., which contributes to Child Health, Community-Based Management Of Acute Malnutrition, Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development, Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition, Treatment Of Severe Acute Malnutrition. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: PCR 2: Child and Maternal Mortality are reduced through more equitable access to quality health, nutrition and WASH interventions
